pageContext.claim: “We charge you essentially nothing [to import a car from China]. It's 2.5 percent, but basically you don't have to -- there are ways around that. So you send a car to us, and you pay nothing. We send a car to you [China], made in the United States, and we have to pay 45 percent tariff.”
pageContext.analysis: China has a 15% tariff on cars.
